<section id="Section596333">
  <title><indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>inventory</primary>
      <secondary>availability by sales order</secondary>
    </indexterm><indexterm significance="normal">
      <primary>sales orders</primary>
      <secondary>inventory availability for</secondary>
    </indexterm>Inventory Availability by Sales Order</title>
  <para id="Para596334">To view Inventory Availability by Sales Order, select
  the "Inventory Availability by Sales Order" option. The following screen
  will appear:</para>
  <para id="Para598464"><screenshot>
      <mediaobject>
        <imageobject>
          <imagedata fileref="images/SO_Disp_invAvailBySO.png"
                     id="Graphic598462" />
        </imageobject>
        <caption id="Caption598465">Inventory Availability by Sales
        Order</caption>
      </mediaobject>
    </screenshot></para>
  <para id="Para598466">When displaying Inventory Availability by Sales Order,
  you are presented with the following options:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598561">Sales Order #</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976c90">
        <para>Enter the Sales Order Number of the Sales Order whose
        Availability you want to view.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598563">Order Date</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976cd8">
        <para>Displays the date the Sales Order was placed.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598564">Cust. Name</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976d20">
        <para>Displays Customer name.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598565">Cust. Phone</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976d68">
        <para>Phone: Displays Customer phone number.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598566">P/O Number</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976db0">
        <para>Displays Purchase Order Number.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598479">Only Show Shortages</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976df8">
        <para>Select to only show Inventory shortages in display. A shortage
        describes Inventory quantity whose Availability is negative.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598482">Availability</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976e40">
        <para>Display lists Inventory Availability by Sales Order, using the
        specified parameters.</para>
        <para id="Para654182">If an available quantity value displays in the
        color orange, this means the actual or projected Quantity on Hand is
        at or below the Reorder Level. If the color is red, the current or
        projected Quantity on Hand is below 0.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
  <para id="Para598484">To the far right of the screen, the following buttons
  are available:</para>
  <variablelist>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598485">CLOSE</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976eac">
        <para>Closes the screen, returning you to the application
        desktop.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para598486">QUERY</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976ef4">
        <para>Select to generate the display, using the specified
        parameters.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
    <varlistentry>
      <term id="Para653758">PRINT</term>
      <listitem id="listitemN0x180ac00N0x1976f3c">
        <para>Runs the report associated with this screen.</para>
      </listitem>
    </varlistentry>
  </variablelist>
